Defendant Lynette L McIntosh in court with attorney Katie B. Kegel.  David John Behm appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
State makes sentencing recommendations. Defense makes sentencing recommendations. Defendant makes statement.


The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

9 MONTHS JAIL - STRAIGHT TIME ;

TERM OF PROBATION:  2 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  

AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.'s ; 
No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
Inform Agent of all prescriptions.
No contact with Kirkland's Home Furnishings.
Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling.


COURT COSTS:  $253.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.

CONDITION TIME: 20 DAYS Huber with release for work, treatment and/or health care release. (5 Days - Credit)  Defendant to report to Huber by 6:00 p.m. on June 15, 2018.
First 14 days Huber with release for work, treatment and/or health care release.
Last 6 Days, Stayed to be used at the Agent's discretion, Agent to determine with or without non-working hours.
